  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "VjVuY2iGM24o/rBRYTKGYiEZX9Y=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Operation Batches on /bytes\n\nOperation batches are stored on Swarm `/bytes`, not in a feed. They are immutable and content-addressed \u2014 the batch reference IS the hash of its encrypted contents.\n\n## Why not feeds\n\nFeeds are mutable pointers. Operation data must never change once written, so batches go directly to `/bytes`. The document manifest feed holds the list of batch references in order.\n\n## Schema (decrypted)\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"op-aaa\",\n    \"index\": 0,\n    \"skip\": 0,\n    \"timestampUtcMs\": \"1712750460000\",\n    \"hash\": \"abc123...\",\n    \"action\": {\n      \"id\": \"act-001\",\n      \"type\": \"CREATE_BUDGET\",\n      \"input\": { \"name\": \"Q1 Budget\", \"year\": 2026 },\n      \"scope\": \"global\",\n      \"context\": {\n        \"signer\": {\n          \"user\": { \"address\": \"0xAlice\", \"networkId\": \"1\" },\n          \"app\": { \"name\": \"connect\", \"key\": \"...\" }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n]\n```\n\n## Fields\n\n- `index`: position in the operation log for the scope\n- `skip`: number of operations reshuffled past during conflict resolution\n- `hash`: integrity check on the operation\n- `action.context.signer`: identifies who signed the operation\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
    }
  },
